{"parentUuid":"b9182206-c445-4e06-be21-8cc25853dedb","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_01VPhiWPUcQsKDjc44gChwnT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VjmkzoZiPA3dGBaKKeHmb5","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /Users/rod/build/begbie-hugo\ngit commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nSwitch responsive images to width-based srcset and add a video thumbnail\n\nBlog thumbnails, hero image, and about image used density (1x/2x) srcset,\nwhich picks purely on device pixel ratio and ignores the fact these\nimages render at very different CSS widths across Bootstrap breakpoints\n(full-width single column below lg, 1/3-3/4 width above it). Replaced\nwith width-descriptor srcset plus a sizes attribute matching the actual\nper-breakpoint column math, and added more width tiers so the browser\ncan pick a properly small file at each breakpoint instead of one of two\ncoarse options.\n\nThe blog post banner had no 2x variant at all and was serving a fixed\n970px image into containers rendering up to ~1096px CSS-wide - retina\ndisplays were getting a blurry banner on every post. Gave it the same\nwidth-tier treatment.\n\nAlso:\n- Swapped hero.html's mask reference from hero-mask-svg.png (48KB\n  raster) to hero-mask-svg.svg (251 bytes) - an SVG of the identical\n  shape already sat unused next to it, just never wired up.\n- Replaced the hero video-popup thumbnail source with battle.jpg,\n  moved into the Hugo asset pipeline with a proper 1x/2x/3x srcset\n  (this one has a fixed CSS box size regardless of breakpoint, so\n  density-based srcset is the right tool here).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nClaude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/REDACTED\nEOF\n)\"\ngit status --short"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":531,"cache_read_input_tokens":171848,"output_tokens":637,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":531,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":131,"output_tokens":637,"cache_read_input_tokens":171848,"cache_creation_input_tokens":531,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":531},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CccV3qYR96SNGZMfTExMV","attributionMcpServer":"plugin:superpowers-chrome:chrome","attributionMcpTool":"use_browser","type":"assistant","uuid":"62b1a4a8-20f0-4671-b042-b2071ff59b7a","timestamp":"2026-07-02T03:00:50.414Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/rod/build/begbie-hugo","sessionId":"8fb9c608-e9d6-441a-a521-ca4f3b79a9b4","version":"2.1.197","gitBranch":"chore/responsive-image-tiers","slug":"mighty-stargazing-mountain"}
