{"type":"pr-link","sessionId":"8fb9c608-e9d6-441a-a521-ca4f3b79a9b4","prNumber":10,"prUrl":"https://github.com/rodbegbie/begbie-hugo/pull/10","prRepository":"rodbegbie/begbie-hugo","timestamp":"2026-07-02T03:02:14.157Z"}
{"parentUuid":"0aa181d6-384c-44b6-8ea5-372282da8fd6","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_01P4LjVLhV2RgMGqHQTkt4zc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RtDzFNMsEWU5TqeY6qeADn","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /Users/rod/build/begbie-hugo\ngh pr create --title \"Right-size responsive images per breakpoint, fix banner blur, shrink hero mask\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\n- Replace density-based (`1x`/`2x`) `srcset` with width-descriptor `srcset` + a `sizes` attribute for the hero image, about image, and both blog thumbnail templates (list + homepage preview). These images render at very different CSS widths across breakpoints (full-width single column below `lg`, a fraction of the container above it) — density descriptors ignore that entirely and just react to DPR, so desktop was often over-served and some tablet/`md` cases were under-served.\n- Give the blog post banner the same treatment. It previously had **no 2x variant at all** — a fixed 970px image into a container rendering up to ~1096px CSS-wide, so retina displays were getting a blurry banner on every single post.\n- Swap `hero.html`'s mask reference from `hero-mask-svg.png` (48KB raster) to `hero-mask-svg.svg` (251 bytes) — an SVG of the identical shape (mirror of `about-mask-svg.svg`) was already sitting on disk, unused.\n- Replace the hero video-popup thumbnail source (`hqdefault.jpg`) with `battle.jpg`, moved into the Hugo asset pipeline with a proper 1x/2x/3x srcset (this one has a fixed CSS box regardless of breakpoint, so density-based srcset is the correct tool there).\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `hugo --quiet` builds clean\n- [x] Verified in-browser that the blog thumbnail picks a smaller image (400w) at a desktop/xxl viewport and a larger one (600w) at a tablet/md viewport — confirms `sizes` is driving selection, not just DPR\n- [x] Visually checked hero mask, about mask, blog thumbnails, and the hypothesis-driven-development banner render correctly locally\n- [ ] Check the Cloudflare Pages preview on a real phone/tablet if possible\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/REDACTED\nEOF\n)\""},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":303,"cache_read_input_tokens":173645,"output_tokens":822,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":303,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":822,"cache_read_input_tokens":173645,"cache_creation_input_tokens":303,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":303},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CccV9pf11EV55PDxm2Ruv","attributionMcpServer":"plugin:superpowers-chrome:chrome","attributionMcpTool":"use_browser","type":"assistant","uuid":"d88025a2-31ee-4e1b-a580-9248d6c39c2d","timestamp":"2026-07-02T03:02:11.358Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/rod/build/begbie-hugo","sessionId":"8fb9c608-e9d6-441a-a521-ca4f3b79a9b4","version":"2.1.197","gitBranch":"chore/responsive-image-tiers","slug":"mighty-stargazing-mountain"}
